perl-Term-Animation
--------------------------------------------
This module provides a framework to produce sprite animations using
ASCII art. Each ASCII 'sprite' is given one or more frames, and
placed into the animation as an 'animation object'. An animation
object can have a callback routine that controls the position and
frame of the object.

Runtime requirements:
  perl-5.8.8-4
  perl-Curses-1.20-1

Canonical homepage:
  http://www.robobunny.com/projects/animation/
  http://search.cpan.org/~kbaucom/Term-Animation/

Canonical download:
  http://www.cpan.org/authors/id/K/KB/KBAUCOM/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack perl-Term-Animation-2.4-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./perl-Term-Animation-2.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/perl-Term-Animation-2.4-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/perl-Term-Animation-2.4-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /etc/postinstall/perl-Term-Animation.sh
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/Term/Animation.pm
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/Term/Animation/Entity.pm
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/cygwin/auto/Term/Animation/.packlist
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/perl-Term-Animation-2.4.README
  /usr/share/doc/perl-Term-Animation-2.4/Changes
  /usr/share/doc/perl-Term-Animation-2.4/MIGRATION
  /usr/share/doc/perl-Term-Animation-2.4/README
  /usr/share/man/man3/Term.Animation.3pm.gz
  /usr/share/man/man3/Term.Animation.Entity.3pm.gz
  /usr/share/perl/cygwin-pods/Term-Animation.pod

